Description: UVSY_BPT4 - Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Plays a role in viral DNA synthesis by promoting enzymatic activities of UvsX recombinase, by promoting UvsX-ssDNA filament assembly, and by helping UvsX to displace bound gp32 from ssDNA. From Enterobacteria phage T4 (Bacteriophage T4).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
